column5: Well it's my last chance for info for eyes at Lady Evelyn Lake,how is the eye fishing doing at or near that lattitude,i,m leaving for Red Pine Wilderness Lodge fri am please help thanks OLERUFF

Just got back from a week fishing Temagami and surrounding area. Fishing was outstanding. Caught every walleye on leeches under a boober in 10 to 12 foot water with bait around 5 to 7 feet down. We were fishing rock shoales near 25 to 30 foot water. Good luck!
